                            "text": "June 11",
                            "type": "calendarDay",
                            "name": "11",
                            "subs": [
                                {
                                    "text": "I have a two-monitor Mac. Sometimes when I move my mouse in the Dock at the bottom of my main monitor, it moves to the bottom of the other monitor.",
                                    "type": "tweet",
                                    "created": "Fri, 11 Jun 2021 13:55:11 GMT",
                                    "tweetId": "1403350098495553540",
                                    "urltweet": "https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1403350098495553540",
                                    "tweetUserName": "davewiner",
                                    "subs": [
                                        {
                                            "text": "All of a sudden I have to stop, launch the  Preferences app, open the Dock panel, click the Right button then the Bottom button, and now the Dock is back where it belongs.",
                                            "type": "tweet",
                                            "created": "Fri, 11 Jun 2021 13:55:11 GMT",
                                            "tweetId": "1403350099359637514",
                                            "urltweet": "https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1403350099359637514",
                                            "inReplyToId": "1403350098495553540",
                                            "tweetUserName": "davewiner",
                                            "subs": [
                                                {
                                                    "text": "It seems the problem could be easily solved by putting a Lock icon on the Dock tab, as they have on other panels. I can't imagine why they thought a mouse gesture should do something so radical as move the Dock.",
                                                    "type": "tweet",
                                                    "created": "Fri, 11 Jun 2021 13:55:11 GMT",
                                                    "tweetId": "1403350100324372483",
                                                    "urltweet": "https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1403350100324372483",
                                                    "inReplyToId": "1403350099359637514",
                                                    "tweetUserName": "davewiner"
                                                }
                                            ]
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
